description:
Cathie Wood joins me today. Is everything you thought you knew about investing is about to change forever? Cathie reveals the best investments to make in 2025 to get rich fast. 

She explains: 
▫️How there’s only 5 years until everything changes, and what you must do to prepare.
▫️Why she’s betting on Bitcoin hitting $1.5 million by 2030.
▫️The simple strategy that will skyrocket your passive income.
▫️How Tesla’s autonomous taxis and humanoid robots will reshape entire industries.
▫️The number one company that could make you financially free in 5 years.

The information in this episode is for educational purposes only and should not be considered financial advice. Always do your own research or speak to a licensed financial advisor before making any investment decisions.

Appreciate you’re not a journalist but it would be cool if you actually questioned some of the wild/ outlandish/ sometimes factually incorrect statements made by the people you interview, e.g here she states Tesla is the largest AI Project on earth - really? On what basis? It has a huge fleet of cars but its data pool is shrinking as more people turn to better and cheaper alternatives (sales in Uk alone are down 45%). It’s certainly not leading the AI race compared to the likes of OpenAi, Meta, and Alphabet (weird there is no mention of Waymo here). It has so much competition on all fronts.

comments.text: I was troubled by the offhand comment that the federal bureaucracy is bloated.  I’m no data expert and I certainly accept if there’s any efficiency everywhere. As I recall the Clinton administration spent some time evaluating staffing and got rid of many jobs supposedly saving us money.  But , to fulfill their functions, the federal government had to hire outside contractors, which in some cases ended up costing more.
